TY  - JOUR
AU  - Lamont, Owen
AU  - Polk, Christopher
AU  - Saaá-Requejo, Jesús
T1  - Financial Constraints and Stock Returns
PY  - 2001
Y1  - 2001/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/14.2.529
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 14
IS  - 2
SP  - 529
EP  - 554
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We test whether the impact of financial constraints on firm value is observable in stock returns. We form portfolios of firms based on observable characteristics related to financial constraints and test for common variation in stock returns. Financially constrained firms’ stock returns move together over time, suggesting that constrained firms are subject to common shocks. Constrained firms have low average stock returns in our 1968–1997 sample of growing manufacturing firms. We find no evidence that the relative performance of constrained firms reflects monetary policy, credit conditions, or business cycles.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/14.2.529
ER  - 



